dmalatesta:
Also:

``` javascript
// Hide the next/previous buttons
$('.' + option.next + ', .' + option.prev, elem).fadeOut(0);
return false;
```

`return false;` stops the `this.each` loop, so the elements after the empty one do not work as expected.
Replacing it with `return;` will do the trick:

``` javascript
// Hide the next/previous buttons
$('.' + option.next + ', .' + option.prev, elem).fadeOut(0);
return;
```

Cheers,
